data.enText: a piece of metal, plastic, etc. on which a door, lid or gate moves freely as it opens or closes
The door had been pulled off its hinges.
to attach sth with a hinge

before.enText: of an action, a result, etc.

data.chText: 一切都取决于这些会谈的结果。
data.enText: Everything hinges on the outcome of these talks.

tr: a joint that holds two parts together so that one can swing relative to the other
a circumstance upon which subsequent events depend
example: his absence is the hinge of our plan

value.def: A hinge is a piece of metal, wood, or plastic that is used to join a door to its frame or to join two things together so that one of them can swing freely.

example.ex: The top swung open on well-oiled hinges.
example.tran: 用润滑良好的铰链固定的盖子一旋转就打开了。
